  <strong><h1><font size="30">Carnation</font> </h1></strong>

<strong>
 The carnation (scientific name: Dianthus caryophyllus)
  carnations, dianthus, also known as Lion's Head, carnations,
   large flower carnation, the Netherlands carnation
  Caryophyllaceae Dianthus plant, located in the temperate zone 
  of Europe and mainland China's Fujian, Hubei and other places
   of origin in the Mediterranean region, is currently the world's 
   most common flowers. The carnations including many varieties and 
hybrids, almost continuous flowering in the greenhouse.Since 1907, began 
a pink carnation as a symbol of Mother's Day, so this is often as dedicated to his mother flowers.
